==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sectary
<hw>Sec"ta*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;<plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Sectaries</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[F. <ets>sectaire</ets>.
See <er>Sect</er>.]</ety> <def>A sectarian; a member or adherent of a
sect; a follower or disciple of some particular teacher in philosophy or
religion; one who separates from an established church; a
dissenter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I never knew that time in England when men of truest religion were
not counted <qex>sectaries</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sectator</ent>⟦br⟧
